SECTION 5: QUALITY & RISK MITIGATION IDEAS

These ideas appeal to risk-averse recruiters wanting to guarantee quality.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

IDEA #21: "Quality Guarantee Dashboard - Only See Candidates Who Will Succeed"

Positioning Message: "Dashboard filters to show only candidates likely to succeed"
Core Value: Pre-vetted candidate quality filtering
Target Audience: Quality-obsessed recruiters, risk-averse organizations
Psychology: Risk elimination = confidence
Key Metric: "88% of dashboard-recommended candidates succeed 6+ months"
Why It Works: Quality is most important to risk-averse recruiters

Implementation:
• Filter: "Show only candidates with 85%+ success probability"
• Result: 15 candidates instead of 500 - all likely to succeed
• Confidence: "Green light = hire confidently"
• Backup: "If hire doesn't work, next 14 candidates also high-probability"
• Messaging: "Stop wasting time on risky candidates - see only the safe bets"

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

IDEA #22: "Retention Intelligence - Hire Candidates Who Will Stay"

Positioning Message: "Know which candidates are likely to stay long-term"
Core Value: Retention probability prediction
Target Audience: Retention-focused companies, cost-conscious recruiters
Psychology: Retention = cost savings
