SECTION 9: CONTENT STRATEGY FOR DASHBOARD POSITIONING

For each positioning idea, create:

Content Type 1: FEATURE SHOWCASE (1 per idea)
└─ Format: 90-second feature demo video
   └─ Show: Dashboard interface, specific insight, decision made
   └─ Result: "Saved 2 hours, hired better candidate"
   └─ CTA: "Try the dashboard"

Content Type 2: USE CASE STORY (1 per idea)
└─ Format: Blog article or LinkedIn post (800-1200 words)
   └─ Story: Recruiter faced problem, dashboard solved it
   └─ Result: Faster hiring, better candidates, data-backed decisions
   └─ CTA: "See how dashboard works"

Content Type 3: DATA VISUALIZATION (1 per idea)
└─ Format: Infographic showing insight
   └─ Example: "Dashboard finds top 1% candidates vs manually finding average"
   └─ Visual: Side-by-side comparison showing time/quality difference
   └─ CTA: "Get dashboard to find your top 1%"

Content Type 4: RECRUITER TESTIMONIAL (2-3 per idea)
└─ Format: Video testimonial (60-90 seconds)
   └─ Quote: "Dashboard saved me 10 hours per hire"
   └─ Result: Faster hiring, better candidates, more confidence
   └─ CTA: "Join 5,000+ recruiters using dashboard"

Content Type 5: COMPARISON CONTENT (1-2 per category)
└─ Format: "Before & After Dashboard"
   └─ Before: Manual hiring process, challenges
   └─ After: Dashboard-powered hiring, results
   └─ ROI: Time saved, quality improved, decisions faster

Content Type 6: INTERACTIVE DEMO (1 per main category)
└─ Format: Interactive tool on website
   └─ Example: "See your hiring opportunity with dashboard"
   └─ Input: Company size, hiring role, current challenges
   └─ Output: "Dashboard shows you could save 30 hours/month"

Total Initial Content: 40-50 pieces across 30 ideas

